  "bookTitle": "Beast Tamers",
  "bookId": 59,
  "firstAcquaintance": "An experienced beast-kin mercenary with a colorful life story. Now she's donned a wedding dress to become a marriage instructor, passing on her hard-won matrimonial wisdom.",
  "personality": "She calls herself a 'marriage instructor,' but really she's just using the title as an excuse to tease young people. With all inhibitions cast aside, Anna is in a thoroughly playful mood.",
  "like": "Romance stories",
  "familiarData": "The guild takes on all kinds of work, so it needs specialists from every field. A marriage expert? Of course they need a beautiful expert to personally guide the inexperienced guild master.\nAnna has experienced the sweetness of a wedding, become a mother, and ultimately been mortgaged by her husband to pay off debts. Having tasted every flavor of marriage, she is undoubtedly well-qualified.\nFailure is the mother of success, and right now Anna is a marriage instructor, guiding newcomers through their wedding ceremonies while sharing her own mistakes so they won't repeat them. But wait, why is she holding an iron ball?\n\n'If you could marry again, what would you choose?'\nShe always laughs and replies, 'Marriage, like age, never gets a do-over.'\nBut when the question changes to 'What if you married the master?' she suddenly has plenty to say. After all, it's hypothetical, so anything she says can be passed off as a joke, even if she accidentally reveals her true feelings.",
